2
00:00:20.433 --> 00:00:22.233
_

3
00:00:23.233 --> 00:00:24.733
_

4
00:00:26.333 --> 00:00:29.633
_

5
00:00:32.227 --> 00:00:33.194
Anne Marie?

6
00:00:36.127 --> 00:00:39.063
Did you find it?

7
00:00:39.097 --> 00:00:41.966
I had to bribe the janitor. Thanks.

8
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.568
I can handle labor.
but not sugar withdrawal.

9
00:00:46.872 --> 00:00:48.572
Sleep tight.

10
00:00:48.607 --> 00:00:50.374
Thank you.

11
00:00:51.143 --> 00:00:54.378
Diego.

12
00:00:56.381 --> 00:00:57.848
You're perfect.

13
00:01:03.355 --> 00:01:05.256
I forgot to ask her for a glass of water.

14
00:01:06.658 --> 00:01:08.993
I'll get you one.

15
00:01:35.987 --> 00:01:38.189
Oh. my goodness. Sister Luisa!

16
00:01:38.788 --> 00:01:40.856
I'm so sorry.

17
00:01:40.890 --> 00:01:42.958
I was on my rounds and
I keep hearing this...

18
00:01:42.992 --> 00:01:44.826
The mice?

19
00:01:44.861 --> 00:01:46.628
It's this old convent.

20
00:01:46.662 --> 00:01:49.598
I still get scared walking alone at night.

21
00:01:49.632 --> 00:01:52.501
Good night. Sister Anne Marie.

22
00:01:52.535 --> 00:01:53.702
Good night.

23
00:02:08.484 --> 00:02:10.152
Hugo?

24
00:02:17.693 --> 00:02:19.628
Martina!

25
00:02:19.662 --> 00:02:21.530
No. No. No! No!

26
00:02:21.564 --> 00:02:23.198
No! Martina!

27
00:02:23.232 --> 00:02:24.366
Martina!

28
00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:25.801
No...

29
00:02:25.835 --> 00:02:27.402
No. Martina?!

30
00:02:27.437 --> 00:02:29.438
Martina...

31
00:02:47.490 --> 00:02:51.990
Synced and corrected by oykubuyuk
www.addic7ed.com

32
00:02:56.933 --> 00:02:58.700
Tea.

33
00:03:05.797 --> 00:03:07.898
Hmm.

34
00:03:07.933 --> 00:03:09.735
Bit traditional for my taste.

35
00:03:09.831 --> 00:03:12.933
But glad to see
your strength's coming back.

36
00:03:16.371 --> 00:03:17.304
Oi.

37
00:03:17.339 --> 00:03:18.906
Hey!

38
00:03:18.940 --> 00:03:20.240
Does it feel good?

39
00:03:20.275 --> 00:03:21.475
Being back at it?

40
00:03:21.509 --> 00:03:23.844
Yes and no.

41
00:03:23.878 --> 00:03:26.013
I've been having nightmares
about this stuff.

42
00:03:26.047 --> 00:03:28.649
It's all I've been able to see
since we got back from Kentucky.

43
00:03:28.683 --> 00:03:30.050
Well. there's no mystery there.

44
00:03:30.085 --> 00:03:31.518
You touch an angel's heart.

45
00:03:31.553 --> 00:03:33.988
you get a blast from the Old Testament.

46
00:03:34.022 --> 00:03:36.056
You're seeing things
that winged menace used to see.

47
00:03:36.091 --> 00:03:37.124
I thought so. too.

48
00:03:37.158 --> 00:03:39.093
Until I drew this.

49
00:03:43.732 --> 00:03:47.635
This twisty little
horror show's an Invunche.

50
00:03:47.669 --> 00:03:49.603
And it's right up that angel's alley.

51
00:03:50.839 --> 00:03:52.139
Must've missed that story

52
00:03:52.173 --> 00:03:54.074
- in Sunday school.
- Invunche don't get

53
00:03:54.109 --> 00:03:55.910
a shout out in the Good Book.

54
00:03:55.944 --> 00:03:57.545
but they ripped a few throats
back in Noah's day.

55
00:03:57.579 --> 00:03:58.846
Believe me.

56
00:03:58.880 --> 00:03:59.947
Nasty bastards.

57
00:03:59.981 --> 00:04:02.316
Unstoppable.

58
00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:04.151
Luckily they all went out
with the last flood.

59
00:04:04.185 --> 00:04:06.654
Give the history lesson a break. eh?

60
00:04:06.688 --> 00:04:08.689
Do the bloody crossword or something.

61
00:04:21.102 --> 00:04:22.469
I'm sorry. I didn't know

62
00:04:22.504 --> 00:04:23.571
John had a visitor.

63
00:04:23.605 --> 00:04:24.805
Where is he? I need him.

64
00:04:24.839 --> 00:04:27.908
John. did you forget someone?

65
00:04:27.943 --> 00:04:29.209
My name is Zed by the way.

66
00:04:29.244 --> 00:04:30.544
I need him now.

67
00:04:30.579 --> 00:04:31.946
Clearly.

68
00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:33.113
John!

69
00:04:33.148 --> 00:04:34.148
John Constantine!

70
00:04:34.182 --> 00:04:36.450
Oh. geez. Good God. woman!

71
00:04:36.484 --> 00:04:38.218
I'm not deaf. all right? I can hear you.

72
00:04:38.253 --> 00:04:39.620
Keep your bloody knickers on.

73
00:04:41.323 --> 00:04:42.823
Anne Marie?

74
00:04:44.759 --> 00:04:46.193
Are you all right?

75
00:04:47.963 --> 00:04:50.798
Would I come to you if I was all right?

76
00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:52.333
You didn't know she was here?

77
00:04:52.367 --> 00:04:54.367
She isn't. Where are you?

78
00:04:54.767 --> 00:04:56.467
Mexico. I need your help.

79
00:04:56.504 --> 00:04:58.105
- Are you hurt?
- No.

80
00:04:58.139 --> 00:04:59.607
Something stole a baby.

81
00:05:01.239 --> 00:05:02.272
It killed the mother.

82
00:05:02.307 --> 00:05:04.808
It ripped into her.

83
00:05:04.843 --> 00:05:07.678
Hey.

84
00:05:07.712 --> 00:05:08.912
What just happened?

85
00:05:08.947 --> 00:05:10.180
Well. I told you she's not here.

86
00:05:10.215 --> 00:05:12.683
"Ripped" how? Teeth or claws?

87
00:05:12.717 --> 00:05:15.118
- This thing have fangs? Fur?
- I don't know.

88
00:05:15.153 --> 00:05:17.387
Then how do you know there's
not a mortal explanation?

89
00:05:22.051 --> 00:05:23.585
I wish it had been human.

90
00:05:23.619 --> 00:05:25.587
I would've gone to someone else for help.

91
00:05:25.621 --> 00:05:27.722
Anyone else.

92
00:05:27.756 --> 00:05:30.058
And what's stopping you?
There's plenty of occult

93
00:05:30.092 --> 00:05:31.826
experts in Mexico.

94
00:05:31.861 --> 00:05:33.194
They don't owe me.

95
00:05:33.229 --> 00:05:35.063
You do.

96
00:05:35.097 --> 00:05:37.565
Avenue Nueva 366.

97
00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:39.100
Villa del Carbón.

98
00:05:39.134 --> 00:05:40.301
Hurry.

99
00:05:43.139 --> 00:05:45.907
Avenue Nueva 366...

100
00:05:45.941 --> 00:05:47.375
What just happened?

101
00:05:47.409 --> 00:05:49.711
It's called bi-location.

102
00:05:49.745 --> 00:05:52.881
The power to be in
two places at the same time.

103
00:05:52.915 --> 00:05:54.883
It's the domain of adventurous souls

104
00:05:54.917 --> 00:05:56.784
and the occasional saint.

105
00:05:56.819 --> 00:05:58.386
which Anne Marie Flynn

106
00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:00.822
most certainly isn't.

107
00:06:00.856 --> 00:06:03.224
She hates my guts.

108
00:06:03.259 --> 00:06:07.128
Must be pretty sodding desperate
to be coming to me for help.

109
00:06:29.863 --> 00:06:31.463
Ow! Bollocks!

110
00:06:31.498 --> 00:06:34.233
You should use a spoon.

111
00:06:34.267 --> 00:06:36.368
Making a purification bowl.

112
00:06:36.402 --> 00:06:38.670
Left my last good one in Puerto Rico.

113
00:06:38.705 --> 00:06:41.006
Does the work of a priest.

114
00:06:41.040 --> 00:06:43.141
Turns water holy.

115
00:06:43.176 --> 00:06:46.044
Well. you know. I could
probably put it in my carry-on

116
00:06:46.079 --> 00:06:47.880
if you need some space.

117
00:06:47.914 --> 00:06:50.082
Well. that would be lovely
if you were going with.

118
00:06:50.116 --> 00:06:53.452
But you're still on R and R.

119
00:06:53.486 --> 00:06:55.654
You're that concerned about me?

120
00:06:55.688 --> 00:06:57.756
That's why I'm letting you crash here.

121
00:06:57.790 --> 00:06:59.658
I'll turn the traps on on my way out.

122
00:06:59.692 --> 00:07:01.994
The house will keep you safe
as long as you don't leave it.

123
00:07:02.028 --> 00:07:03.495
Okay.

124
00:07:03.529 --> 00:07:05.964
ll. just have. you know. one more question.

125
00:07:09.269 --> 00:07:12.070
I...

126
00:07:12.105 --> 00:07:14.206
You're seriously not taking
the Spanish speaker?

127
00:07:14.240 --> 00:07:17.609
I'm seriously not going there
for a conversation.

128
00:07:17.644 --> 00:07:18.944
Ah-ha!

129
00:07:18.978 --> 00:07:21.213
So. she is an old flame.

130
00:07:22.615 --> 00:07:25.284
We slept together... once

131
00:07:25.318 --> 00:07:27.319
if that's what you're after.

132
00:07:27.353 --> 00:07:28.654
Never should have though.

133
00:07:29.855 --> 00:07:32.457
Wasn't the point of us.

134
00:07:33.792 --> 00:07:37.028
Magic was my salvation growing up.

135
00:07:37.062 --> 00:07:39.697
She hooked me up in the occult scene.

136
00:07:39.732 --> 00:07:41.899
Is that why you "owe" her?

137
00:07:43.002 --> 00:07:45.169
No.

138
00:07:45.204 --> 00:07:47.438
She was with me at Newcastle.

139
00:07:48.640 --> 00:07:51.042
She saw what happened.

140
00:07:51.076 --> 00:07:53.277
Just like Gary.

141
00:07:53.312 --> 00:07:55.680
Swore she'd kill me if
she ever saw me again.

142
00:07:55.714 --> 00:07:58.916
I'd rather play this one out in private.

143
00:07:58.951 --> 00:08:00.651
if you don't mind.

144
00:08:02.020 --> 00:08:03.855
Sounds like Chas.

145
00:08:03.889 --> 00:08:05.857
So much for privacy. huh?

146
00:08:05.891 --> 00:08:07.291
Ah. don't take it personally. luv.

147
00:08:07.326 --> 00:08:09.594
Chas and I. we go way back.

148
00:08:09.628 --> 00:08:11.396
Remember. stay inside.

149
00:08:11.430 --> 00:08:14.165
And. uh. don't go wandering.

150
00:08:33.130 --> 00:08:35.432
Did you know we were coming to a convent?

151
00:08:35.435 --> 00:08:37.235
It's one gory detail she left out.

152
00:08:50.083 --> 00:08:51.283
You should have brought Zed.

153
00:08:51.318 --> 00:08:52.952
Don't you bloody start on me.

154
00:08:52.986 --> 00:08:54.487
Uh. excuse me. luv?

155
00:08:54.521 --> 00:08:55.955
You don't happen to know
a British girl by the name

156
00:08:55.989 --> 00:08:58.424
of Anne Marie Flynn. do you?
Fairly pretty. brunette.

157
00:08:58.458 --> 00:09:00.326
She kind of got this...

158
00:09:02.028 --> 00:09:03.262
Annie?

159
00:09:03.296 --> 00:09:04.864
Están conmigo.

160
00:09:04.898 --> 00:09:06.165
Gracias.

161
00:09:06.199 --> 00:09:08.167
Uh. it's great to see you.

162
00:09:08.201 --> 00:09:10.236
John didn't need to drag you into this.

163
00:09:10.270 --> 00:09:12.138
I should've told him to come alone.

164
00:09:12.172 --> 00:09:14.807
That's another thing you should've told me.

165
00:09:14.841 --> 00:09:17.076
Sister.

166
00:09:17.110 --> 00:09:20.379
We can't talk here.

167
00:09:27.634 --> 00:09:28.436
The police outside work

168
00:09:28.534 --> 00:09:30.068
for the man whose wife was murdered.

169
00:09:30.137 --> 00:09:31.738
They questioned everyone
who was here last night.

170
00:09:31.772 --> 00:09:33.640
No one saw anything.

171
00:09:33.674 --> 00:09:35.608
By the look of the burn on your chest.

172
00:09:35.643 --> 00:09:39.078
we're not looking for a human suspect.

173
00:09:39.113 --> 00:09:42.048
It's gonna take more than an
interrogation to find out what.

174
00:09:42.083 --> 00:09:43.883
The police will be leaving
for the funeral soon.

175
00:09:43.918 --> 00:09:45.652
You'll have an hour to look around.

176
00:09:45.686 --> 00:09:47.287
Oh. come on. luv.

177
00:09:47.321 --> 00:09:50.090
You're skipping all the juicy parts.

178
00:09:51.427 --> 00:09:54.562
No. I told you exactly what I saw.

179
00:09:54.597 --> 00:09:56.165
You can't just sit there
in a bloody nun's habit.

180
00:09:56.199 --> 00:09:58.800
and pretend we don't have nothing to cover.

181
00:09:58.898 --> 00:10:00.365
I always figured

182
00:10:00.400 --> 00:10:02.067
that one of us would flee to Mexico.

183
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:05.137
but I thought there'd be tequila involved.

184
00:10:05.171 --> 00:10:07.372
Or skinny-dipping.

185
00:10:08.007 --> 00:10:10.008
More jokes.

186
00:10:10.042 --> 00:10:11.476
That's incredible.

187
00:10:11.511 --> 00:10:12.644
What happened to Astra

188
00:10:12.678 --> 00:10:14.346
didn't change you at all.

189
00:10:16.249 --> 00:10:17.916
Easy. Annie...

190
00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:19.084
Don't call me that.

191
00:10:19.118 --> 00:10:21.086
I don't know how you do it.

192
00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:23.622
but my soul can't take another lost child.

193
00:10:23.656 --> 00:10:26.358
I took a vow of service

194
00:10:26.392 --> 00:10:28.493
to repent for my sins during that séance.

195
00:10:28.528 --> 00:10:30.162
What about you?

196
00:10:31.764 --> 00:10:33.431
Just because I'm not hiding in a nunnery

197
00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:36.101
don't mean I ignore my debts.

198
00:10:37.770 --> 00:10:40.005
Sometimes I even fly to
Mexico on a moment's notice

199
00:10:40.039 --> 00:10:41.373
to very little thanks.

200
00:10:41.407 --> 00:10:42.607
Thanks?

201
00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:44.176
Oh. is that why you're here?

202
00:10:44.210 --> 00:10:46.745
I'm fresh out. but you
should try the others.

203
00:10:46.779 --> 00:10:48.413
Ritchie. Gary.

204
00:10:48.447 --> 00:10:50.148
Judith...

205
00:10:50.183 --> 00:10:51.516
Have they called you with their gratitude?

206
00:10:55.154 --> 00:10:57.222
There's no point reeling
in the years. now. is there?

207
00:10:58.758 --> 00:11:00.892
We need to figure out
what kind of demonic killer

208
00:11:00.927 --> 00:11:03.261
walks into the house of God
without breaking a sweat.

209
00:11:48.137 --> 00:11:49.938
Is this the only place it attacked?

210
00:11:49.972 --> 00:11:51.773
Yes.

211
00:12:06.722 --> 00:12:07.889
That's from the mice.

212
00:12:07.924 --> 00:12:10.125
Not necessarily.

213
00:12:10.159 --> 00:12:13.061
A lot of wall-dwellers target children.

214
00:12:13.095 --> 00:12:14.429
Duendes. fairies...

215
00:12:14.463 --> 00:12:17.399
nursery demons.

216
00:12:17.433 --> 00:12:19.601
Grab the table. Chas.

217
00:12:19.635 --> 00:12:22.003
Our first job is to narrow
down the category.

218
00:12:22.038 --> 00:12:24.773
Rune stones will tell us which team

219
00:12:24.807 --> 00:12:26.541
our culprit plays for.

220
00:12:53.836 --> 00:12:55.971
Oh! Uh... hello.

221
00:12:56.005 --> 00:12:58.139
Can I help you?

222
00:12:58.174 --> 00:12:59.975
It's all right. Sister.
They're just here to...

223
00:13:00.009 --> 00:13:01.343
Crime scene cleanup.

224
00:13:01.377 --> 00:13:03.745
Yes. There's a new mother coming in soon.

225
00:13:03.779 --> 00:13:06.515
Of course. Sorry to interrupt.

226
00:13:06.549 --> 00:13:08.516
One of the sisters saw you.

227
00:13:08.551 --> 00:13:10.619
She thought you were El Cuycuy.

228
00:13:10.653 --> 00:13:12.287
The bogeyman.

229
00:13:12.321 --> 00:13:13.622
Huh.

230
00:13:13.656 --> 00:13:15.290
And you just charged up here

231
00:13:15.324 --> 00:13:16.725
with nothing but your wits.

232
00:13:17.660 --> 00:13:19.194
Woman after my own heart.

233
00:13:20.830 --> 00:13:23.532
Good luck.

234
00:13:23.566 --> 00:13:24.766
You. too.

235
00:13:27.603 --> 00:13:30.172
You can't even turn it off
around a woman married to God?

236
00:13:31.101 --> 00:13:34.203
What. you mean Sister
Flirtatious? She started it.

237
00:13:34.237 --> 00:13:35.771
If those cops are gonna be back

238
00:13:35.806 --> 00:13:37.707
in an hour. we gotta move fast.

239
00:13:53.423 --> 00:13:55.558
Holy mother of earth.

240
00:13:55.592 --> 00:13:57.760
mother of the higher realm.

241
00:13:57.794 --> 00:14:00.129
guide my hand.

242
00:14:00.163 --> 00:14:02.698
Reveal the evil that dwelt here.

243
00:14:09.506 --> 00:14:11.007
What have we here?

244
00:14:17.447 --> 00:14:19.148
Whatever was here covered its tracks.

245
00:14:19.182 --> 00:14:22.051
Baby snackers aren't that
sophisticated. This is good.

246
00:14:22.085 --> 00:14:23.719
It means the kid might still be alive.

247
00:14:23.754 --> 00:14:25.087
We need a link

248
00:14:25.122 --> 00:14:26.922
to the child's soul.

249
00:14:26.957 --> 00:14:29.025
The placenta. It's buried
in their backyard.

250
00:14:29.059 --> 00:14:30.393
Local tradition.

251
00:14:30.427 --> 00:14:32.328
It's supposed to bring good luck.

252
00:14:32.362 --> 00:14:34.830
Fat lot of good that did.
All right. you stay here.

253
00:14:34.865 --> 00:14:37.400
Watch for trouble.
We've got some digging to do.

254
00:14:38.735 --> 00:14:40.402
If the placenta's really buried

255
00:14:40.437 --> 00:14:42.672
in Hugo's back yard. I can find it myself.

256
00:14:42.706 --> 00:14:44.640
One spell will tell me if the tyke's alive.

257
00:14:44.675 --> 00:14:46.575
You can wait in the van.

258
00:14:46.610 --> 00:14:48.144
if you're afraid.

259
00:14:48.178 --> 00:14:49.378
Who said that I was afraid?

260
00:14:49.413 --> 00:14:50.613
Well. I figured it was that

261
00:14:50.647 --> 00:14:51.881
or you just took a spontaneous

262
00:14:51.915 --> 00:14:53.115
vow of silence on the ride over.

263
00:14:53.150 --> 00:14:54.583
It couldn't possibly be

264
00:14:54.618 --> 00:14:57.086
that I'm focused on finding a missing baby?

265
00:14:57.120 --> 00:14:59.021
Or that I don't have
anything to say to you?

266
00:14:59.056 --> 00:15:00.322
Annie. listen...

267
00:15:01.758 --> 00:15:02.992
I know you don't trust me

268
00:15:03.026 --> 00:15:05.094
- after the séance at Newcastle.
- "Trust."

269
00:15:05.128 --> 00:15:07.096
You lost that before the séance.

270
00:15:09.766 --> 00:15:12.565
When you left my bed and went
trawling for girls at the bar?

271
00:15:13.366 --> 00:15:15.734
My sheets weren't even cold. John.

272
00:15:15.768 --> 00:15:16.969
Yeah.

273
00:15:17.003 --> 00:15:18.637
I saw you.

274
00:15:19.939 --> 00:15:22.441
Do you want that vow of silence back now?

275
00:15:49.502 --> 00:15:51.737
I didn't mean for you to see me that night.

276
00:15:54.107 --> 00:15:55.674
I'm sorry I hurt you.

277
00:15:55.708 --> 00:15:59.178
It's not just the sex or the séance. John.

278
00:15:59.212 --> 00:16:00.812
It's... it's your ego.

279
00:16:00.847 --> 00:16:03.248
Everyone's just a port in your storm.

280
00:16:17.797 --> 00:16:20.332
The placenta's definitely buried here.

281
00:16:22.635 --> 00:16:24.736
Is that skin?

282
00:16:33.479 --> 00:16:34.846
Oh...

283
00:16:39.775 --> 00:16:40.973
Oh. my God.

284
00:16:43.475 --> 00:16:44.876
Manos arriba! Hands where I can see them!

285
00:16:44.910 --> 00:16:47.178
- Hugo. wait! It's me!
- Sister?

286
00:16:47.213 --> 00:16:48.980
What are you doing?

287
00:16:49.014 --> 00:16:50.515
What is that?

288
00:16:50.549 --> 00:16:52.650
A piece of human fruit. mate.

289
00:16:52.685 --> 00:16:54.485
Your baby's alive.

290
00:16:55.487 --> 00:16:57.755
And I know who took him.

291
00:17:03.590 --> 00:17:05.291
Have another.

292
00:17:05.325 --> 00:17:06.926
It won't make more sense.

293
00:17:06.960 --> 00:17:09.695
but it will make you more open to it.

294
00:17:13.186 --> 00:17:15.621
I'll be "open" to my trees

295
00:17:15.655 --> 00:17:17.556
growing human flesh?

296
00:17:17.592 --> 00:17:20.161
The placenta is
connected to an infant's soul.

297
00:17:20.195 --> 00:17:22.696
Your son's is telling us
that there's some...

298
00:17:22.731 --> 00:17:24.732
very dark magic surrounding him.

299
00:17:24.766 --> 00:17:26.435
As old as the Garden of Eden.

300
00:17:26.469 --> 00:17:28.003
Forbidden fruit. that ring a bell?

301
00:17:28.037 --> 00:17:29.504
If you try to tell me

302
00:17:29.539 --> 00:17:32.274
that Adam or Eve took my boy...

303
00:17:32.308 --> 00:17:33.976
Not Eve.

304
00:17:34.010 --> 00:17:35.544
One of her sisters.

305
00:17:36.978 --> 00:17:38.812
They turned down Adam's proposal

306
00:17:38.847 --> 00:17:41.615
before Eve said yes.

307
00:17:41.649 --> 00:17:43.517
Chose an eternity as goddesses of hell

308
00:17:43.551 --> 00:17:46.520
over a lifetime of obedience on Earth.

309
00:17:46.554 --> 00:17:49.256
It's hard to blame 'em. really.

310
00:17:50.054 --> 00:17:51.655
Martina was a good Catholic.

311
00:17:51.689 --> 00:17:54.524
Why would God let this
happen to her. to Diego?

312
00:17:54.559 --> 00:17:56.727
This isn't God's work. Hugo.

313
00:17:58.753 --> 00:18:03.323
Evil wins when we let it destroy
our faith in the power of good.

314
00:18:03.352 --> 00:18:05.320
Believe me. I know how hard it is.

315
00:18:06.856 --> 00:18:08.990
I've been on the force for 14 years.

316
00:18:10.551 --> 00:18:12.685
Never felt so helpless.

317
00:18:13.950 --> 00:18:15.721
I always thought God was listening.

318
00:18:17.054 --> 00:18:18.921
Ah. let the Almighty take His time out.

319
00:18:18.956 --> 00:18:21.991
We got plenty to occupy ourselves with.

320
00:18:22.025 --> 00:18:24.393
like figuring out
which one of Eve's sisters

321
00:18:24.428 --> 00:18:25.795
is behind all this.

322
00:18:29.099 --> 00:18:30.967
Now you're standing in for God.

323
00:18:31.001 --> 00:18:33.336
Make way for John Constantine.

324
00:18:33.370 --> 00:18:34.971
I'm telling a desperate man

325
00:18:35.005 --> 00:18:36.305
that there are things we can do

326
00:18:36.340 --> 00:18:38.274
to get his son back other than pray.

327
00:18:38.308 --> 00:18:40.710
Your arrogance is out of control.

328
00:18:45.302 --> 00:18:47.270
It took another baby.

329
00:18:55.302 --> 00:18:56.536
Considering a blue period?

330
00:18:56.570 --> 00:18:58.171
- Hey!
- Hi.

331
00:18:58.205 --> 00:19:00.373
Eddie. Sorry. I...

332
00:19:00.408 --> 00:19:02.242
didn't recognize you with. um.

333
00:19:02.276 --> 00:19:03.476
your clothes on.

334
00:19:04.745 --> 00:19:06.079
What are you doing here?

335
00:19:06.113 --> 00:19:07.680
Well. I'm only modeling

336
00:19:07.715 --> 00:19:09.682
until my art career takes off.

337
00:19:09.717 --> 00:19:11.684
You paint. too?

338
00:19:11.719 --> 00:19:14.354
I'll tell you about it over drinks.

339
00:19:14.388 --> 00:19:16.456
First round's on me?

340
00:19:16.490 --> 00:19:18.491
Let me pay for these. first.

341
00:19:31.507 --> 00:19:33.774
I finished my MBA three years ago.

342
00:19:33.809 --> 00:19:35.843
I don't know. I can't bring myself

343
00:19:35.878 --> 00:19:37.845
to put on a tie and go to work.

344
00:19:38.981 --> 00:19:40.648
So you strip naked and pose nude.

345
00:19:40.682 --> 00:19:41.749
Oh. yeah. it's a cry for help.

346
00:19:44.386 --> 00:19:46.721
So what about you?
How long you been studying art?

347
00:19:46.755 --> 00:19:48.155
It's my first class.

348
00:19:48.190 --> 00:19:49.724
No. I don't believe that.

349
00:19:49.758 --> 00:19:51.292
I... I saw your sketches.

350
00:19:53.128 --> 00:19:56.630
Drawing... it's like breathing to me.

351
00:19:56.665 --> 00:19:58.432
Hmm.

352
00:19:58.467 --> 00:19:59.901
I'd love to see your work.

353
00:20:01.269 --> 00:20:02.503
No. you wouldn't.

354
00:20:03.572 --> 00:20:05.206
You really wouldn't.

355
00:20:11.613 --> 00:20:13.414
That beer go to your head?

356
00:20:16.652 --> 00:20:19.086
No. No. I...

357
00:20:19.121 --> 00:20:21.489
promise I'm not that much of a lightweight.

358
00:20:21.523 --> 00:20:23.290
Ah. okay. That sounds like a challenge.

359
00:20:23.325 --> 00:20:24.692
Hey. why don't we do

360
00:20:24.726 --> 00:20:26.360
the next round at my place?

361
00:20:28.430 --> 00:20:29.630
Okay.

362
00:20:31.466 --> 00:20:33.200
Why didn't I wake up?

363
00:20:33.235 --> 00:20:34.869
It's good that you didn't.

364
00:20:34.903 --> 00:20:36.537
It may have saved your life.

365
00:20:36.571 --> 00:20:38.139
We're going to find her.

366
00:20:38.173 --> 00:20:39.407
We'll start by dusting for prints.

367
00:20:39.441 --> 00:20:41.208
There won't be any prints.

368
00:20:43.742 --> 00:20:47.341
_

369
00:20:47.741 --> 00:20:49.241
_

370
00:20:50.140 --> 00:20:51.643
_

371
00:20:52.640 --> 00:20:55.344
_

372
00:20:56.244 --> 00:20:58.940
_

373
00:20:58.947 --> 00:21:00.145
_

374
00:21:01.747 --> 00:21:02.914
Oi!

375
00:21:02.948 --> 00:21:03.948
So. uh...

376
00:21:03.983 --> 00:21:06.250
if I'm reading this right.

377
00:21:06.285 --> 00:21:08.319
this teenager's your son.

378
00:21:08.353 --> 00:21:11.122
and the new missing baby is...

379
00:21:11.156 --> 00:21:12.724
your granddaughter.

380
00:21:13.492 --> 00:21:14.726
Did you piss off a Gypsy. mate?

381
00:21:14.760 --> 00:21:17.495
Get your whole brood cursed?

382
00:21:19.098 --> 00:21:20.198
The killer is targeting your family.

383
00:21:20.232 --> 00:21:23.134
You two just. uh. carry on catching up.

384
00:21:23.169 --> 00:21:25.236
I got a guilty goddess to catch.

385
00:21:25.271 --> 00:21:26.671
Does that fountain outside work?

386
00:21:36.295 --> 00:21:38.796
I can't let you summon some deity from hell

387
00:21:38.831 --> 00:21:39.398
on the convent grounds.

388
00:21:39.431 --> 00:21:40.765
I'm only casting a spell to invoke

389
00:21:40.799 --> 00:21:42.166
the goddess' reflection in the water.

390
00:21:42.201 --> 00:21:43.835
That way. I can put a name to the face.

391
00:21:43.869 --> 00:21:45.736
And what happens when your spell
gets out of control. John?

392
00:21:45.771 --> 00:21:47.238
This convent's full of innocent people.

393
00:21:47.272 --> 00:21:49.741
Then why did you call me?

394
00:21:49.775 --> 00:21:51.909
Saving lives requires choices
that you're not willing to make.

395
00:21:51.944 --> 00:21:54.178
or I wouldn't be here.

396
00:21:54.213 --> 00:21:56.047
Now go and pray and let me work.

397
00:22:01.620 --> 00:22:03.588
Was that really necessary?

398
00:22:15.133 --> 00:22:18.535
I've heard worse from him.

399
00:22:18.570 --> 00:22:21.271
He'd rather risk your feelings
than any other part of you.

400
00:22:21.306 --> 00:22:24.041
That's how...

401
00:22:24.075 --> 00:22:26.143
he deals with the pain.

402
00:22:27.433 --> 00:22:29.135
John has one thing

403
00:22:29.231 --> 00:22:30.765
that makes his life worth a damn.

404
00:22:30.831 --> 00:22:32.432
and he can't do it
if he lets anyone in too close.

405
00:22:34.432 --> 00:22:36.266
Like he did with you.

406
00:22:45.710 --> 00:22:47.277
That's all.

407
00:22:49.915 --> 00:22:51.849
All right. sisters of Eve.

408
00:22:53.383 --> 00:22:57.252
Whichever one of you is hanging around.

409
00:22:57.287 --> 00:23:00.389
it's time to reveal your pretty mug.

410
00:23:12.687 --> 00:23:16.056
Axis mundi. produco tuus vires.

411
00:23:16.091 --> 00:23:17.758
Axis mundi. produco

412
00:23:17.792 --> 00:23:19.259
tuus vires.

413
00:23:23.765 --> 00:23:25.532
Hola. sister.

414
00:23:25.567 --> 00:23:28.702
I'm. uh. involved
in a personal prayer here.

415
00:23:28.737 --> 00:23:30.904
if you don't mind clearing out a sec.

416
00:23:30.939 --> 00:23:32.172
Uh. we need you upstairs.

417
00:23:32.207 --> 00:23:33.807
Yolanda is very upset.

418
00:23:33.842 --> 00:23:36.043
You left everyone in confusion.

419
00:23:36.077 --> 00:23:37.911
Oh. you just tell them to relax. all right?

420
00:23:37.946 --> 00:23:39.013
We'll get everything sorted.

421
00:23:39.047 --> 00:23:41.248
If you don't come with me now.

422
00:23:41.282 --> 00:23:43.650
you'll be the one sorted out.

423
00:23:43.685 --> 00:23:44.685
By Mother Superior.

424
00:23:44.719 --> 00:23:46.653
Or the police.

425
00:23:49.057 --> 00:23:50.624
It's funny. your timing here.

426
00:23:50.658 --> 00:23:52.960
You know. if I didn't know better.

427
00:23:52.994 --> 00:23:55.996
I'd say you're trying to keep me
away from this here fountain.

428
00:23:57.599 --> 00:23:58.666
Let's go.

429
00:23:58.700 --> 00:24:00.067
Now.

430
00:24:00.101 --> 00:24:02.069
Okay.

431
00:24:02.103 --> 00:24:04.371
I'll just rinse out my bowl.

432
00:24:14.749 --> 00:24:17.518
Forgive me. Sister.

433
00:24:17.552 --> 00:24:20.287
Your name slipped my mind.

434
00:24:21.456 --> 00:24:22.856
Lillith. is it?

435
00:24:22.891 --> 00:24:24.191
Durgia.

436
00:24:24.225 --> 00:24:26.660
Naamah.

437
00:24:26.695 --> 00:24:28.262
Lamashtu.

438
00:24:33.868 --> 00:24:35.402
Where are the babies?

439
00:25:12.889 --> 00:25:14.790
Wow. You live here by yourself?

440
00:25:14.825 --> 00:25:16.459
I'm house-sitting.

441
00:25:17.794 --> 00:25:20.229
Well. you have very interesting friends.

442
00:25:20.264 --> 00:25:23.432
Yes. I do have very interesting friends.

443
00:25:23.467 --> 00:25:25.768
Whoa!

444
00:25:25.802 --> 00:25:26.903
It's nice. right?

445
00:25:26.937 --> 00:25:27.970
Yeah.

446
00:25:28.005 --> 00:25:29.138
Yeah.

447
00:25:38.782 --> 00:25:40.850
I can't wait for you to meet
them when they get home.

448
00:25:40.884 --> 00:25:42.752
They love interrogations.

449
00:25:42.786 --> 00:25:44.186
Why are you following me?

450
00:25:46.189 --> 00:25:47.990
Your father wants you home.

451
00:25:50.394 --> 00:25:52.562
What did you say?

452
00:25:52.596 --> 00:25:55.965
We just want to talk to you. Mary.

453
00:25:55.999 --> 00:25:59.035
Don't you ever. ever call me that again!

454
00:26:02.306 --> 00:26:03.606
Her name isn't Louisa.

455
00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:05.007
It's Lamashtu.

456
00:26:05.042 --> 00:26:07.043
Eve's youngest sister

457
00:26:07.077 --> 00:26:09.011
and a bit of a glorified vampire.

458
00:26:09.046 --> 00:26:10.479
I taught you about Lamashtu.

459
00:26:10.514 --> 00:26:12.315
She doesn't kidnap her prey.

460
00:26:13.650 --> 00:26:15.017
What does she do?

461
00:26:16.490 --> 00:26:18.324
Lamashtu enjoys babies

462
00:26:18.358 --> 00:26:21.060
for their nutritional value.

463
00:26:21.094 --> 00:26:24.030
But lucky for you. she's
curbing her hunger.

464
00:26:24.064 --> 00:26:25.231
though I can't conceive why.

465
00:26:25.265 --> 00:26:26.866
Lamashtu lives to feed.

466
00:26:26.900 --> 00:26:28.501
Maybe the question is...

467
00:26:28.535 --> 00:26:30.469
what makes Hugo's litter
worth keeping alive?

468
00:26:30.504 --> 00:26:31.904
We're nobodies. good Catholics.

469
00:26:31.938 --> 00:26:34.206
I've got nothing to hide from you.

470
00:26:34.241 --> 00:26:36.075
Maybe someone's hiding something from you.

471
00:26:36.109 --> 00:26:38.378
And what about the rest of your family?

472
00:26:38.412 --> 00:26:39.512
Who knows your roots?

473
00:26:39.547 --> 00:26:40.880
How about my grandmother. Pia.

474
00:26:40.915 --> 00:26:42.716
She was born in Chile.

475
00:26:42.750 --> 00:26:44.084
Great. I have a way with older women.

476
00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:51.558
Thank you. abuelita.

477
00:26:51.592 --> 00:26:54.027
Is that Mateo?

478
00:26:54.061 --> 00:26:55.996
No. no. I'm just a friend of Hugo's.

479
00:26:56.030 --> 00:26:58.098
I have some questions about Chile.

480
00:26:58.132 --> 00:27:00.100
He said that you're the expert.

481
00:27:00.134 --> 00:27:02.902
- Chile?
- Pia. listen to me.

482
00:27:02.937 --> 00:27:04.804
Something is coming after our babies.

483
00:27:04.839 --> 00:27:07.040
Something inhuman.

484
00:27:07.074 --> 00:27:09.274
Martina is dead. abuelita.

485
00:27:11.074 --> 00:27:13.543
Why would someone be targeting us?

486
00:27:13.577 --> 00:27:15.545
God help us.

487
00:27:17.047 --> 00:27:18.948
They are back.

488
00:27:18.982 --> 00:27:21.284
Who is. Mrs. Lopez?

489
00:27:21.318 --> 00:27:23.886
La Brujeria.

490
00:27:23.921 --> 00:27:26.289
La Brujeria?

491
00:27:28.592 --> 00:27:30.526
They are tracking us down.

492
00:27:30.561 --> 00:27:32.295
Gathering new blood.

493
00:27:32.329 --> 00:27:35.298
I've never heard of La Brujeria.

494
00:27:35.332 --> 00:27:38.000
They were powerful warlocks in
Chile long before it was Chile.

495
00:27:38.035 --> 00:27:41.470
It's prehistoric stuff...
they've been gone for eons.

496
00:27:41.505 --> 00:27:43.272
No. not gone.

497
00:27:43.307 --> 00:27:46.309
In hiding.

498
00:27:46.343 --> 00:27:48.078
How come I've never heard of them?

499
00:27:48.144 --> 00:27:50.012
Because they don't exist anymore.

500
00:27:50.047 --> 00:27:52.114
When I was a girl.

501
00:27:52.149 --> 00:27:57.286
my grandfather was one of those monsters.

502
00:27:58.644 --> 00:28:01.246
They live to cause pain.

503
00:28:01.344 --> 00:28:05.413
My father ran away for all of us.

504
00:28:12.688 --> 00:28:15.023
Don't add up.

505
00:28:15.057 --> 00:28:17.092
Brujeria wielded a magic
the world hasn't seen

506
00:28:17.126 --> 00:28:18.794
since God turned on the lights.

507
00:28:18.828 --> 00:28:19.995
He struck them down.

508
00:28:20.029 --> 00:28:21.429
Not even hell would give them asylum.

509
00:28:21.464 --> 00:28:22.431
They were annihilated.

510
00:28:22.465 --> 00:28:23.431
You don't believe her?

511
00:28:23.466 --> 00:28:25.434
I can't believe them.

512
00:28:25.468 --> 00:28:27.536
I don't have a spell to shut
down the Brujeria. Anne Marie.

513
00:28:27.570 --> 00:28:28.737
Nobody does.

514
00:28:28.771 --> 00:28:29.838
She's speaking gibberish.

515
00:28:29.872 --> 00:28:31.072
Then why are you scared?

516
00:28:31.107 --> 00:28:32.841
I'm not scared.

517
00:28:32.875 --> 00:28:34.876
If the Brujeria were back.
we'd know it. all right?

518
00:28:34.911 --> 00:28:36.611
It wouldn't be subtle. there would be...

519
00:28:39.682 --> 00:28:40.649
Bugger me.

520
00:28:40.683 --> 00:28:41.650
What is it?

521
00:28:41.684 --> 00:28:43.618
The rising darkness.

522
00:28:43.653 --> 00:28:48.023
it's. uh. what I checked myself
out of the asylum to fight.

523
00:28:49.625 --> 00:28:51.593
If the Brujeria are behind it...

524
00:28:54.330 --> 00:28:56.965
I can see it now... it's
not that you don't care.

525
00:28:56.999 --> 00:28:59.601
it's that you can't care about
anybody and do what you do.

526
00:29:03.973 --> 00:29:06.208
I think I did come here to hide.

527
00:29:06.242 --> 00:29:08.710
And it doesn't work.

528
00:29:08.745 --> 00:29:10.112
Under this disguise.

529
00:29:10.146 --> 00:29:12.113
I'm the same scared girl
I was at Newcastle.

530
00:29:16.786 --> 00:29:18.086
Disguise.

531
00:29:18.121 --> 00:29:21.323
If Lamashtu wants a baby with Hugo's blood.

532
00:29:21.357 --> 00:29:23.825
then I say we give her one.

533
00:29:27.343 --> 00:29:29.778
Once we fill the poultry with Hugo's blood.

534
00:29:29.813 --> 00:29:33.815
I'll use a glamour spell to
make it look like an infant.

535
00:29:33.850 --> 00:29:36.585
We'll hand it off to our evil lady friend.

536
00:29:36.619 --> 00:29:39.821
and she will kindly lead us
to her baby stash.

537
00:29:39.856 --> 00:29:41.423
If Lamashtu is working for the Brujeria.

538
00:29:41.458 --> 00:29:42.991
you'd be walking right onto their radar.

539
00:29:43.026 --> 00:29:45.160
Well. I didn't say there weren't risks.

540
00:29:45.195 --> 00:29:48.130
How do you know she won't attack you first?

541
00:29:48.164 --> 00:29:50.132
I'll present the baby
as a mother's offering.

542
00:29:50.166 --> 00:29:52.134
She'll have no reason to hurt me.

543
00:29:52.168 --> 00:29:53.469
You tried to kill Lamashtu.

544
00:29:53.503 --> 00:29:54.770
She won't come near you.

545
00:29:54.804 --> 00:29:56.305
No. that's a good point.

546
00:29:56.339 --> 00:29:58.640
I'll have to dress as a woman.

547
00:29:58.675 --> 00:30:01.210
Just need me a skirt and a wig.

548
00:30:01.244 --> 00:30:03.579
- Stop it.
- Stop what?

549
00:30:03.613 --> 00:30:05.747
This kind of pathetic ruse might
have worked with Gary Lester.

550
00:30:05.782 --> 00:30:07.916
but I think I deserve
a little more respect.

551
00:30:07.951 --> 00:30:11.520
I have no idea what
you're talking about. luv.

552
00:30:11.554 --> 00:30:12.921
You need me to make this offering.

553
00:30:12.956 --> 00:30:14.223
You're counting on it.

554
00:30:18.495 --> 00:30:21.430
Look. we had our shot at life. Annie.

555
00:30:21.464 --> 00:30:23.966
We've made our mistakes.
but these... these are...

556
00:30:24.000 --> 00:30:25.501
they're babies.

557
00:30:27.237 --> 00:30:30.839
No price is too high to save the innocent.

558
00:30:32.342 --> 00:30:34.309
Thank you for your honesty.

559
00:30:38.146 --> 00:30:40.214
I'll make the handoff.

560
00:31:04.857 --> 00:31:06.825
You don't need to fight.

561
00:31:06.859 --> 00:31:09.194
Our father wants what's best for you.

562
00:31:09.228 --> 00:31:12.697
Oh. so he's your father. too. now. is he?

563
00:31:12.732 --> 00:31:14.066
Funny.

564
00:31:14.100 --> 00:31:16.401
I don't remember you from my childhood.

565
00:31:16.436 --> 00:31:18.003
Maybe it's because

566
00:31:18.037 --> 00:31:19.805
I spent most of it

567
00:31:19.839 --> 00:31:21.473
in a locked room.

568
00:31:21.507 --> 00:31:22.541
That was for your protection.

569
00:31:22.575 --> 00:31:23.975
You know what you mean to us.

570
00:31:24.010 --> 00:31:25.210
You're our salvation.

571
00:31:25.244 --> 00:31:26.511
Eddie.

572
00:31:26.546 --> 00:31:29.047
Is that even your real name?

573
00:31:30.216 --> 00:31:32.651
How did you find me?

574
00:31:32.685 --> 00:31:34.219
We're the Crusade.

575
00:31:34.253 --> 00:31:36.088
Our believers are everywhere.

576
00:31:36.122 --> 00:31:38.323
We will always find you.

577
00:31:39.625 --> 00:31:42.094
Damn it. Eddie!

578
00:31:42.128 --> 00:31:44.696
You led them up here?

579
00:31:44.730 --> 00:31:46.732
You don't know what they are!

580
00:31:56.259 --> 00:31:57.860
One more step.

581
00:31:57.894 --> 00:31:59.261
and I'll kill him.

582
00:32:01.864 --> 00:32:03.832
I'm so sorry.

583
00:32:03.866 --> 00:32:07.269
You should be. Could've made
this much easier on all of us.

584
00:32:07.303 --> 00:32:08.437
Awake

585
00:32:08.471 --> 00:32:09.504
or asleep?

586
00:32:09.539 --> 00:32:12.574
Your choice.

587
00:32:12.609 --> 00:32:14.710
May be a few minutes
before Lamashtu arrives.

588
00:32:14.744 --> 00:32:17.379
but she'll sniff out the blood.

589
00:32:17.413 --> 00:32:19.514
Now. do you remember the words?

590
00:32:19.549 --> 00:32:21.483
Take this child into your dark womb

591
00:32:21.517 --> 00:32:23.051
and give it eternal life.

592
00:32:25.888 --> 00:32:28.090
You know...

593
00:32:28.124 --> 00:32:30.592
you know you never had

594
00:32:30.627 --> 00:32:32.361
anything to repent for.

595
00:32:32.395 --> 00:32:35.397
Newcastle.

596
00:32:35.431 --> 00:32:37.833
That was my failure.

597
00:32:37.867 --> 00:32:40.135
You don't owe nothing for that.

598
00:32:40.169 --> 00:32:42.271
You're wrong. John.

599
00:32:42.305 --> 00:32:45.741
I owe an anxious 15-year-old boy
with no self worth.

600
00:32:45.775 --> 00:32:48.377
Always hiding from your father

601
00:32:48.411 --> 00:32:50.746
and aching for a mum.

602
00:32:50.780 --> 00:32:52.447
Should've shagged you then. but instead

603
00:32:52.482 --> 00:32:55.150
I introduced you to my world.

604
00:32:55.184 --> 00:32:58.287
It was a world of wonders.

605
00:32:58.321 --> 00:33:00.722
Which you followed into hell.

606
00:33:02.358 --> 00:33:04.293
You are my failure. John.

607
00:33:06.821 --> 00:33:10.257
It's a matter of perspective.

608
00:33:14.596 --> 00:33:15.563
What is this?

609
00:33:15.596 --> 00:33:18.030
The icon of Pazuzu.

610
00:33:18.065 --> 00:33:19.732
It's a bastardly demon.

611
00:33:19.766 --> 00:33:22.502
Used to be Lamashtu's soul mate.

612
00:33:22.536 --> 00:33:24.170
But now she hates his guts.

613
00:33:25.539 --> 00:33:27.340
I can relate.

614
00:34:26.595 --> 00:34:29.631
Take this child into your dark womb

615
00:34:29.695 --> 00:34:32.967
and give it eternal life.

616
00:35:21.448 --> 00:35:22.648
She fell for it.

617
00:35:22.682 --> 00:35:23.682
Of course she did.

618
00:35:24.851 --> 00:35:26.652
Hugo. no.

619
00:35:33.023 --> 00:35:34.524
Hugo. stop!

620
00:35:34.558 --> 00:35:35.726
Hugo. Hugo.

621
00:35:35.821 --> 00:35:37.255
If you want to see your son alive.

622
00:35:37.289 --> 00:35:38.723
you got to let us do what we do. Look.

623
00:35:38.757 --> 00:35:40.792
I know your heart's in the right place.

624
00:35:40.826 --> 00:35:42.627
but you'll kill him.

625
00:35:42.661 --> 00:35:44.629
Okay. go. Go. Go. Take-take this!

626
00:35:44.663 --> 00:35:46.498
No. I have no use for that. I'll take it.

627
00:36:46.621 --> 00:36:48.457
I'm guessing that
our lady friend just discovered

628
00:36:48.520 --> 00:36:50.588
that her baby is really a bloody chicken.

629
00:36:50.622 --> 00:36:52.256
It's not a good idea to split up.

630
00:36:52.290 --> 00:36:55.226
We have to. We can't lose her now.

631
00:36:55.260 --> 00:36:57.094
If you need me. scream.

632
00:36:57.129 --> 00:37:00.464
That won't be a problem for me.

633
00:37:21.686 --> 00:37:23.187
Shh.

634
00:37:51.630 --> 00:37:54.131
I knew that spell wouldn't last forever.

635
00:37:54.165 --> 00:37:56.033
The Pazuzu icon. Give it to me.

636
00:38:02.040 --> 00:38:04.141
Bring me the young bruja.

637
00:38:04.175 --> 00:38:05.442
John. give me Diego.

638
00:38:08.880 --> 00:38:10.347
The way I see it.

639
00:38:10.382 --> 00:38:13.150
I've got something you're
supposed to deliver intact.

640
00:38:13.184 --> 00:38:14.485
Am I wrong?

641
00:38:14.519 --> 00:38:16.253
John. that's an innocent child.

642
00:38:16.288 --> 00:38:18.522
You're working for the Brujeria. Why?

643
00:38:20.058 --> 00:38:22.192
If you don't answer me.

644
00:38:22.227 --> 00:38:24.328
so help me God. I will snap the neck

645
00:38:24.362 --> 00:38:26.197
of your precious little cargo.

646
00:38:26.231 --> 00:38:28.165
and then you'll have to explain
to them why you failed.

647
00:38:28.200 --> 00:38:30.401
Now. why are you working for the Brujeria?

648
00:38:30.435 --> 00:38:33.003
They're expanding my domain.

649
00:38:33.038 --> 00:38:34.605
In hell?

650
00:38:34.639 --> 00:38:35.940
On earth.

651
00:38:35.974 --> 00:38:37.741
John. don't do this.

652
00:38:37.776 --> 00:38:39.276
Don't play this game.

653
00:38:39.311 --> 00:38:41.478
- How? What's their plan?
- Not now.

654
00:38:43.515 --> 00:38:45.950
Or maybe I'll just drown the kid. eh?

655
00:38:45.984 --> 00:38:47.618
John. stop this! Give me Diego now!

656
00:38:47.652 --> 00:38:49.553
You've got three seconds
to tell me what kind

657
00:38:49.588 --> 00:38:50.888
of mayhem they're gonna unleash.

658
00:38:50.922 --> 00:38:52.656
What is their plan?!

659
00:38:52.691 --> 00:38:55.091
They've figured out
how to break the boundary.

660
00:38:55.691 --> 00:38:57.859
Hell and earth will become one.

661
00:38:57.891 --> 00:38:59.425
No more hiding like cowards

662
00:38:59.460 --> 00:39:01.227
in the shadows. We'll live

663
00:39:01.261 --> 00:39:03.930
in the open. and you'll be the ones hiding.

664
00:39:03.964 --> 00:39:06.799
But there'll be no hiding from us.

665
00:39:06.834 --> 00:39:09.035
You'll be ours.

666
00:39:10.237 --> 00:39:12.105
So that's what's on the way.

667
00:39:13.407 --> 00:39:15.308
Ambitious.

668
00:39:16.510 --> 00:39:18.277
Too bad you won't see it.

669
00:39:18.312 --> 00:39:20.580
You don't have the power to stop me.

670
00:39:20.614 --> 00:39:22.248
No man does.

671
00:39:22.283 --> 00:39:25.618
I bet your old mate Pazuzu
sees things differently.

672
00:39:25.653 --> 00:39:28.454
How 'bout I just leave
you two lovebirds to...

673
00:39:28.489 --> 00:39:29.689
sort it out. eh?

674
00:39:29.723 --> 00:39:32.091
Kaskassu sutu ilu.

675
00:39:32.126 --> 00:39:33.626
il Pazuzu.

676
00:39:34.862 --> 00:39:36.229
Kunu...

677
00:39:39.934 --> 00:39:41.601
bel-palluhi

678
00:39:41.635 --> 00:39:44.937
nabu kunu utukku!

679
00:39:57.129 --> 00:39:57.863
John?!

680
00:39:57.930 --> 00:40:00.164
We're alive! We're on our way!

681
00:40:01.600 --> 00:40:03.301
I'll take care of them from here.

682
00:40:30.528 --> 00:40:32.829
Time to go home now.

683
00:40:32.864 --> 00:40:34.231
No!

684
00:40:34.265 --> 00:40:36.800
No!

685
00:40:40.171 --> 00:40:41.839
- Is everybody okay?
- Right as rain.

686
00:40:41.873 --> 00:40:43.006
mate.

687
00:40:43.041 --> 00:40:45.075
Go. Now.

688
00:40:52.016 --> 00:40:53.532
Is there another one?

689
00:41:07.962 --> 00:41:09.229
What is that?

690
00:41:09.264 --> 00:41:10.430
It can't be.

691
00:41:11.799 --> 00:41:13.734
An Invunche.

692
00:41:13.768 --> 00:41:16.303
- We have to run.
- No. no. no. no. no. no.

693
00:41:16.337 --> 00:41:17.771
It'll just attack us.

694
00:41:17.805 --> 00:41:19.673
We can't outrun it.

695
00:41:19.707 --> 00:41:22.509
What do we do?

696
00:41:22.544 --> 00:41:24.678
I...

697
00:41:24.712 --> 00:41:26.914
I've got no idea.

698
00:41:33.821 --> 00:41:36.924
No. no. no. You shoot that gun.
it's gonna attack us for sure.

699
00:41:36.958 --> 00:41:39.560
No. John.

700
00:41:39.594 --> 00:41:41.662
It will attack you.

701
00:41:43.564 --> 00:41:46.667
No price is too high to save the innocent.

702
00:41:47.802 --> 00:41:51.705
Oh. you're a quick study. luv.

703
00:42:08.223 --> 00:42:10.857
Chas?!

703
00:42:11.305 --> 00:43:11.476
